&lt;div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose of this document is to illustrate the steps we followed to compute &lt;a href="http://www.red.com/"&gt;RED&lt;/a&gt; colourspaces primaries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The most important attribute used to specify an &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RGB_color_space"&gt;RGB colourspace&lt;/a&gt; is the set of 3 chromaticities or primaries encompassing the &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gamut"&gt;gamut&lt;/a&gt; of colours that the &lt;em&gt;RGB&lt;/em&gt; colourspace can represent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A convenient way to view an &lt;em&gt;RGB&lt;/em&gt; colourspace gamut is to project it onto a &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chromaticity"&gt;chromaticity diagram&lt;/a&gt; such as the &lt;em&gt;CIE 1931 Chromaticity Diagram&lt;/em&gt; where the primaries define the triangle encompassing the gamut.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
